docs.name: Minneapolis Hard Red Spring Wheat Futures, March 1989 (MWH1989)
docs.description:
Hard red spring wheat is one of the highest protein wheats grown and is sought by millers because of its high quality.
        It is found in bagels, high quality breads and cereals.  Contract Unit: 5,000 bushels. Deliverable Grades: No. 2 or better Northern Spring Wheat with a protein content of 13.5% or higher, with 13% protein deliverable at a discount..

docs.name: AMX Index Futures, May 2014 (FMXK2014)
docs.description:
Market:	NYSE Liffe Amsterdam. NYSE Liffe’s European Derivatives markets list futures contracts on leading European indices. 
      These include the AEX®, BEL20®, CAC40®, FTSE 100® and PSI 20® indices, as well as the FTSEurofirst®, FTSE 250® and FTSE EPRA/NAREIT® indices. 
      Futures are also available on the AEX, CAC 40 and FTSE 100 dividend indices. Unit of trading: 50. Contract Size: Contract valued at €50 per index point (eg value €25,000 at 500).

docs.name: CAC40 Index Mini Futures, May 2014 (MFCK2014)
docs.description: Market: NYSE Liffe Paris.The future contracts are used extensively as price discovery and risk management tools by producers, exporters, trade-houses, refiners and manufacturers. In addition, they are actively traded by managed funds, institutional investors and proprietary traders looking for exposure to soft and agricultural commodity markets. Unit of trading: Index points. Contract Size: Contract valued at € 1 per index point.

docs.name: JGB Futures, September 2014 (JGBU2014)
docs.description: Market: NYSE Liffe London.The future contracts are used extensively as price discovery and risk management tools by producers, exporters, trade-houses, refiners and manufacturers. In addition, they are actively traded by managed funds, institutional investors and proprietary traders looking for exposure to soft and agricultural commodity markets. Unit of trading: ¥100,000,000 nominal value notional long term JGB with 6% coupon. Quotation: Per ¥100 face value.

docs.name: Nikkei 225 VI Futures, August 2014 (NKVIQ2014)
docs.description: Nikkei 225 VI Futures, August 2014. Nikkei 225 VI Futures are futures contracts based on the Nikkei Stock Average Volatility Index (Nikkei 225 VI), which is an index, calculated by Nikkei Inc., estimating the degree of expected fluctuation in the Nikkei Stock Average. Underlying Index:	Nikkei Stock Average Volatility Index (Nikkei 225 VI). Contract Unit:	Nikkei 225 VI × ¥10,000

docs.name: OSE DJIA Futures, December 2014 (DJIAZ2014)

Underlying Index:	Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA). Contract Unit:	DJIA × ¥100
